{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017wJT6Hsv66EMQ2PrWjESv4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21\n     2→\n     3→### 0-1-sprint-state-live-updates — verify (2026-03-21T07:55Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Bug found and fixed:** `parseRalphStatus()` in `migration.ts` was missing the new `currentStory`, `currentPhase`, `lastAction`, `acProgress` fields added by this story. Migration test was failing. Fixed by adding null defaults to the return object.\n     6→- **Observability gap:** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all `codeharness progress` CLI invocations. The progress command doesn't emit structured logs.\n     7→\n     8→### 0-2-ralph-progress-display — verify (2026-03-21T08:00Z)\n     9→\n    10→- **Proof format issue:** AC3 initially reused evidence from AC2 without its own `bash` code block, causing `codeharness verify` to report 3/4 ACs. Fixed by adding a distinct bash block.\n    11→- **No BATS tests in container:** `ralph/tests/` not included in npm package. Verification relied on direct function invocation with mock data.\n    12→- **VictoriaLogs query syntax:** `_stream_id:*` pattern invalid for VictoriaLogs. Used `*` wildcard instead.\n    13→\n    14→### 0-3-run-command-dashboard — verify (2026-03-21T08:04Z)\n    15→\n    16→- **Minor format deviations:** Story specified checkmark/cross prefixes but implementation uses `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` tags. Functionally equivalent, passed verification.\n    17→- **Architecture difference:** Story specified `DashboardFormatter` class but implementation uses Ink React components. Same functionality, different design.\n    18→\n    19→### 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver — verify (2026-03-21T08:09Z)\n    20→\n    21→- Clean verification — all 4 ACs passed without issues.\n    22→\n    23→### 0-5-2-stream-event-parser — verify (2026-03-21T10:35Z)\n    24→\n    25→- **Infrastructure fix:** `parseStreamLine` was not exported from `src/index.ts`, making it inaccessible in the container's dist bundle. Added re-export to `src/index.ts` and rebuilt.\n    26→- **ESM import workaround:** Container requires `VITEST=1` env var to suppress CLI auto-parse on module import. Uses `node --input-type=module` for ESM.\n    27→- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all parser invocations — `parseStreamLine` is a pure function with no telemetry.\n    28→- **Non-standard status from previous session:** Sprint status had `verified` (not a valid status). Normalized to `verifying` before proceeding.\n    29→- All 6 ACs passed black-box verification after infrastructure fix.\n    30→\n    31→---\n    32→\n    33→## Session 2 — Started 2026-03-21T10:44Z\n    34→\n    35→### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — create-story (2026-03-21T10:47Z)\n    36→\n    37→- **Ambiguity: No formal epic definition file for Epic 6.** Derived intent from story name, UX spec, and existing code.\n    38→- **Workaround: Cost field source unclear.** Story assumes `result` events contain cost data — needs verification during implementation.\n    39→- **Risk: AC10 snapshot test fragility.** Softened to \"matches spec format structure\" rather than literal character comparison.\n    40→- **Observation:** Old `epic-6-retrospective.md` documents Brownfield Onboarding epic, not Dashboard Visualization Rework — stale/misleading.\n    41→\n    42→### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — dev-story (2026-03-21T10:56Z)\n    43→\n    44→- **Workaround: file split to avoid circular imports** — NFR9 300-line limit forced a 3-file split. `ink-app.tsx` composes `ink-components.tsx` and `ink-activity-components.tsx` to avoid circular deps. Adds indirection.\n    45→- **Cost accumulation edge case** — `result` event cost only accumulates when `state.sprintInfo` is non-null. Cost from early events before sprint state init is lost.\n    46→- **Iteration count delay** — `currentIterationCount` in run.ts is a mutable closure variable, updated from stderr parsing. Iteration count updates are delayed until next 5-second polling interval.\n    47→- **Missing artifacts** — AGENTS.md, exec-plan, and proof document not created (not in story tasks).\n    48→\n    49→### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — code-review (2026-03-21T11:01Z)\n    50→\n    51→- **HIGH bug fixed:** `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling — cost display would flash and disappear. Fixed with field preservation.\n    52→- **MEDIUM bug fixed:** `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches (e.g., story `3-2` matching `3-20`). Fixed to exact comparison.\n    53→- **LOW unfixed:** `run.ts` is 308 lines (8 over NFR9 300-line limit). Pre-existing.\n    54→- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for full run→renderer→component pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles.\n    55→- **Architecture concern:** Renderer accumulates cost internally with no external read path. `updateSprintState` has implicit merge behavior.\n    56→\n    57→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"81bb0af8-322d-4529-9f90-f01a7df366b2","uuid":"c36f64dc-a5d7-4490-96bb-b2a48662e82d","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:04:29.606Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21\n\n### 0-1-sprint-state-live-updates — verify (2026-03-21T07:55Z)\n\n- **Bug found and fixed:** `parseRalphStatus()` in `migration.ts` was missing the new `currentStory`, `currentPhase`, `lastAction`, `acProgress` fields added by this story. Migration test was failing. Fixed by adding null defaults to the return object.\n- **Observability gap:** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all `codeharness progress` CLI invocations. The progress command doesn't emit structured logs.\n\n### 0-2-ralph-progress-display — verify (2026-03-21T08:00Z)\n\n- **Proof format issue:** AC3 initially reused evidence from AC2 without its own `bash` code block, causing `codeharness verify` to report 3/4 ACs. Fixed by adding a distinct bash block.\n- **No BATS tests in container:** `ralph/tests/` not included in npm package. Verification relied on direct function invocation with mock data.\n- **VictoriaLogs query syntax:** `_stream_id:*` pattern invalid for VictoriaLogs. Used `*` wildcard instead.\n\n### 0-3-run-command-dashboard — verify (2026-03-21T08:04Z)\n\n- **Minor format deviations:** Story specified checkmark/cross prefixes but implementation uses `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` tags. Functionally equivalent, passed verification.\n- **Architecture difference:** Story specified `DashboardFormatter` class but implementation uses Ink React components. Same functionality, different design.\n\n### 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver — verify (2026-03-21T08:09Z)\n\n- Clean verification — all 4 ACs passed without issues.\n\n### 0-5-2-stream-event-parser — verify (2026-03-21T10:35Z)\n\n- **Infrastructure fix:** `parseStreamLine` was not exported from `src/index.ts`, making it inaccessible in the container's dist bundle. Added re-export to `src/index.ts` and rebuilt.\n- **ESM import workaround:** Container requires `VITEST=1` env var to suppress CLI auto-parse on module import. Uses `node --input-type=module` for ESM.\n- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all parser invocations — `parseStreamLine` is a pure function with no telemetry.\n- **Non-standard status from previous session:** Sprint status had `verified` (not a valid status). Normalized to `verifying` before proceeding.\n- All 6 ACs passed black-box verification after infrastructure fix.\n\n---\n\n## Session 2 — Started 2026-03-21T10:44Z\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — create-story (2026-03-21T10:47Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity: No formal epic definition file for Epic 6.** Derived intent from story name, UX spec, and existing code.\n- **Workaround: Cost field source unclear.** Story assumes `result` events contain cost data — needs verification during implementation.\n- **Risk: AC10 snapshot test fragility.** Softened to \"matches spec format structure\" rather than literal character comparison.\n- **Observation:** Old `epic-6-retrospective.md` documents Brownfield Onboarding epic, not Dashboard Visualization Rework — stale/misleading.\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — dev-story (2026-03-21T10:56Z)\n\n- **Workaround: file split to avoid circular imports** — NFR9 300-line limit forced a 3-file split. `ink-app.tsx` composes `ink-components.tsx` and `ink-activity-components.tsx` to avoid circular deps. Adds indirection.\n- **Cost accumulation edge case** — `result` event cost only accumulates when `state.sprintInfo` is non-null. Cost from early events before sprint state init is lost.\n- **Iteration count delay** — `currentIterationCount` in run.ts is a mutable closure variable, updated from stderr parsing. Iteration count updates are delayed until next 5-second polling interval.\n- **Missing artifacts** — AGENTS.md, exec-plan, and proof document not created (not in story tasks).\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — code-review (2026-03-21T11:01Z)\n\n- **HIGH bug fixed:** `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling — cost display would flash and disappear. Fixed with field preservation.\n- **MEDIUM bug fixed:** `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches (e.g., story `3-2` matching `3-20`). Fixed to exact comparison.\n- **LOW unfixed:** `run.ts` is 308 lines (8 over NFR9 300-line limit). Pre-existing.\n- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for full run→renderer→component pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles.\n- **Architecture concern:** Renderer accumulates cost internally with no external read path. `updateSprintState` has implicit merge behavior.\n\n","numLines":57,"startLine":1,"totalLines":57}}}
