{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vq4igZjZhdjs4hXZx9WoJg","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"81bb0af8-322d-4529-9f90-f01a7df366b2","uuid":"81de60e8-1bc6-4d5e-a159-b81ba3fb4a64","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:04:36.380Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — code-review (2026-03-21T11:01Z)\n\n- **HIGH bug fixed:** `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling — cost display would flash and disappear. Fixed with field preservation.\n- **MEDIUM bug fixed:** `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches (e.g., story `3-2` matching `3-20`). Fixed to exact comparison.\n- **LOW unfixed:** `run.ts` is 308 lines (8 over NFR9 300-line limit). Pre-existing.\n- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for full run→renderer→component pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles.\n- **Architecture concern:** Renderer accumulates cost internally with no external read path. `updateSprintState` has implicit merge behavior.","newString":"### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — code-review (2026-03-21T11:01Z)\n\n- **HIGH bug fixed:** `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling — cost display would flash and disappear. Fixed with field preservation.\n- **MEDIUM bug fixed:** `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches (e.g., story `3-2` matching `3-20`). Fixed to exact comparison.\n- **LOW unfixed:** `run.ts` is 308 lines (8 over NFR9 300-line limit). Pre-existing.\n- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for full run→renderer→component pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles.\n- **Architecture concern:** Renderer accumulates cost internally with no external read path. `updateSprintState` has implicit merge behavior.\n\n---\n\n## Session 3 — Started 2026-03-21T11:04Z","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21\n\n### 0-1-sprint-state-live-updates — verify (2026-03-21T07:55Z)\n\n- **Bug found and fixed:** `parseRalphStatus()` in `migration.ts` was missing the new `currentStory`, `currentPhase`, `lastAction`, `acProgress` fields added by this story. Migration test was failing. Fixed by adding null defaults to the return object.\n- **Observability gap:** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all `codeharness progress` CLI invocations. The progress command doesn't emit structured logs.\n\n### 0-2-ralph-progress-display — verify (2026-03-21T08:00Z)\n\n- **Proof format issue:** AC3 initially reused evidence from AC2 without its own `bash` code block, causing `codeharness verify` to report 3/4 ACs. Fixed by adding a distinct bash block.\n- **No BATS tests in container:** `ralph/tests/` not included in npm package. Verification relied on direct function invocation with mock data.\n- **VictoriaLogs query syntax:** `_stream_id:*` pattern invalid for VictoriaLogs. Used `*` wildcard instead.\n\n### 0-3-run-command-dashboard — verify (2026-03-21T08:04Z)\n\n- **Minor format deviations:** Story specified checkmark/cross prefixes but implementation uses `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` tags. Functionally equivalent, passed verification.\n- **Architecture difference:** Story specified `DashboardFormatter` class but implementation uses Ink React components. Same functionality, different design.\n\n### 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver — verify (2026-03-21T08:09Z)\n\n- Clean verification — all 4 ACs passed without issues.\n\n### 0-5-2-stream-event-parser — verify (2026-03-21T10:35Z)\n\n- **Infrastructure fix:** `parseStreamLine` was not exported from `src/index.ts`, making it inaccessible in the container's dist bundle. Added re-export to `src/index.ts` and rebuilt.\n- **ESM import workaround:** Container requires `VITEST=1` env var to suppress CLI auto-parse on module import. Uses `node --input-type=module` for ESM.\n- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all parser invocations — `parseStreamLine` is a pure function with no telemetry.\n- **Non-standard status from previous session:** Sprint status had `verified` (not a valid status). Normalized to `verifying` before proceeding.\n- All 6 ACs passed black-box verification after infrastructure fix.\n\n---\n\n## Session 2 — Started 2026-03-21T10:44Z\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — create-story (2026-03-21T10:47Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity: No formal epic definition file for Epic 6.** Derived intent from story name, UX spec, and existing code.\n- **Workaround: Cost field source unclear.** Story assumes `result` events contain cost data — needs verification during implementation.\n- **Risk: AC10 snapshot test fragility.** Softened to \"matches spec format structure\" rather than literal character comparison.\n- **Observation:** Old `epic-6-retrospective.md` documents Brownfield Onboarding epic, not Dashboard Visualization Rework — stale/misleading.\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — dev-story (2026-03-21T10:56Z)\n\n- **Workaround: file split to avoid circular imports** — NFR9 300-line limit forced a 3-file split. `ink-app.tsx` composes `ink-components.tsx` and `ink-activity-components.tsx` to avoid circular deps. Adds indirection.\n- **Cost accumulation edge case** — `result` event cost only accumulates when `state.sprintInfo` is non-null. Cost from early events before sprint state init is lost.\n- **Iteration count delay** — `currentIterationCount` in run.ts is a mutable closure variable, updated from stderr parsing. Iteration count updates are delayed until next 5-second polling interval.\n- **Missing artifacts** — AGENTS.md, exec-plan, and proof document not created (not in story tasks).\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — code-review (2026-03-21T11:01Z)\n\n- **HIGH bug fixed:** `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling — cost display would flash and disappear. Fixed with field preservation.\n- **MEDIUM bug fixed:** `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches (e.g., story `3-2` matching `3-20`). Fixed to exact comparison.\n- **LOW unfixed:** `run.ts` is 308 lines (8 over NFR9 300-line limit). Pre-existing.\n- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for full run→renderer→component pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles.\n- **Architecture concern:** Renderer accumulates cost internally with no external read path. `updateSprintState` has implicit merge behavior.\n\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":54,"oldLines":3,"newStart":54,"newLines":7,"lines":[" - **Coverage gap:** No integration test for full run→renderer→component pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles."," - **Architecture concern:** Renderer accumulates cost internally with no external read path. `updateSprintState` has implicit merge behavior."," ","+---","+","+## Session 3 — Started 2026-03-21T11:04Z","+"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
