{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019M1XCCihCL1SQRsxjJuP7P","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 6-1: Rewrite Ink Components to Match UX Spec\n     2→\n     3→## Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As an operator watching `codeharness run --live`,\n     8→I want the terminal display to match the UX specification exactly,\n     9→so that the output looks professional, consistent, and matches the documented design.\n    10→\n    11→## Goal\n    12→\n    13→The Ink terminal renderer output must visually match the UX spec mockup in `_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-specification.md` lines 197-253. Every prior implementation diverged from the spec. This story requires literal reproduction of the spec format.\n    14→\n    15→## Context: Why This Keeps Failing\n    16→\n    17→Previous sessions \"interpreted\" the visual format instead of reproducing it literally. The current Header uses an Ink `Box` with `borderStyle=\"round\"` and `borderColor=\"cyan\"` — the spec shows a plain text header line with `━━━` separators. The StoryBreakdown uses a compact summary format (`N ✓ done`) — the spec shows labeled sections on separate lines (`Done:`, `This:`, `Next:`, `Blocked:`). This story bridges the gap between spec and implementation.\n    18→\n    19→## Target Output (from UX spec — reproduce EXACTLY)\n    20→\n    21→### Running state:\n    22→```\n    23→codeharness run | iteration 3 | 47m elapsed | $12.30 spent\n    24→━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n    25→Story: 3-2-bmad-installation-workflow-patching\n    26→Phase: verify → AC 8/12 (docker exec ... codeharness init --json)\n    27→\n    28→Done: 3-1 ✓  4-1 ✓  4-2 ✓\n    29→This: 3-2 ◆ verifying (8/12 ACs)\n    30→Next: 3-3 (verifying, no proof yet)\n    31→\n    32→Blocked: 0-1 ✕ (10/10)  13-3 ✕ (10/10)\n    33→━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n    34→```\n    35→\n    36→### Story completion:\n    37→```\n    38→[OK] Story 3-2: DONE — 12/12 ACs verified\n    39→  └ Proof: verification/3-2-proof.md\n    40→  └ Duration: 18m | Cost: $4.20\n    41→[INFO] Sprint: 18/65 done (28%) — moving to 3-3\n    42→```\n    43→\n    44→### Story returned to dev:\n    45→```\n    46→[WARN] Story 3-3: verification found 2 failing ACs → returning to dev\n    47→  └ AC 3: bridge --dry-run output missing epic headers\n    48→  └ AC 7: bridge creates duplicate beads issues\n    49→  └ Attempt 2/10 — dev will fix and re-verify\n    50→```\n    51→\n    52→## Acceptance Criteria\n    53→\n    54→- [x] AC1: Header line renders as `codeharness run | iteration N | Xm elapsed | $Y.ZZ spent` — plain text, NO Ink Box border, NO `borderStyle`, NO `◆` prefix <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    55→- [x] AC2: `━━━` separator line rendered below header and below story breakdown, spanning terminal width (no Ink Box border) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    56→- [x] AC3: `Story:` and `Phase:` rendered on separate lines below header separator, with `Phase:` including AC progress (`AC N/M`) and current command <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    57→- [x] AC4: Story breakdown uses labeled sections on separate lines: `Done:` with individual short keys + `✓`, `This:` with current story + `◆` + AC progress, `Next:` with next pending, `Blocked:` with `✕` and retry counts in parens <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    58→- [x] AC5: Story completion messages render as `[OK] Story {key}: DONE — {N}/{M} ACs verified` with `└` detail lines for proof path, duration, and cost <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    59→- [x] AC6: Story warning/failure messages render as `[WARN] Story {key}: ...` with `└` detail lines for failing AC descriptions and attempt count <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    60→- [x] AC7: Cost tracking field (`totalCost`) added to `SprintInfo` type, sourced from stream-json `result` events (accumulated per session), displayed as `$Y.ZZ spent` in header <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    61→- [x] AC8: Iteration number field (`iterationCount`) added to `SprintInfo` type, sourced from ralph stderr `[LOOP]` messages, displayed as `iteration N` in header <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    62→- [x] AC9: All existing ink-renderer tests updated to match new component structure — zero test regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    63→- [x] AC10: Visual snapshot test added — renders a known state and asserts output matches spec format (header line, separators, labeled story sections) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    64→\n    65→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    66→\n    67→- [x] Task 1: Rewrite Header component to match spec (AC: #1, #2, #7, #8)\n    68→  - [x] Remove `<Box borderStyle=\"round\" borderColor=\"cyan\" paddingX={1}>` wrapper\n    69→  - [x] Render header as plain `<Text>` line: `codeharness run | iteration {N} | {elapsed} elapsed | ${cost} spent`\n    70→  - [x] Add `iterationCount?: number` and `totalCost?: number` to `SprintInfo` type\n    71→  - [x] Render `━━━` separator as a `<Text>` line using `━` repeated to `process.stdout.columns || 60`\n    72→  - [x] Render `Story:` and `Phase:` on separate lines below separator\n    73→  - [x] Add `acProgress?: string` (e.g., `8/12`) and `currentCommand?: string` to `SprintInfo`\n    74→  - [x] Format Phase line as `Phase: {phase} → AC {acProgress} ({currentCommand})`\n    75→\n    76→- [x] Task 2: Rewrite StoryBreakdown to match spec layout (AC: #4)\n    77→  - [x] Change from horizontal compact format to vertical labeled sections\n    78→  - [x] `Done:` line — list each done story as `{shortKey} ✓` separated by two spaces\n    79→  - [x] `This:` line — show current story as `{shortKey} ◆ {status} ({acProgress} ACs)`\n    80→  - [x] `Next:` line — show next pending story with status hint\n    81→  - [x] `Blocked:` line — show blocked stories as `{shortKey} ✕ ({retryCount}/{maxRetries})`\n    82→  - [x] Add `retryCount?: number` and `maxRetries?: number` to `StoryStatusEntry` type\n    83→  - [x] Render bottom `━━━` separator after story breakdown\n    84→\n    85→- [x] Task 3: Parse iteration count from ralph stderr (AC: #8)\n    86→  - [x] Add `[LOOP]` pattern match to `parseIterationMessage()` in `run-helpers.ts`\n    87→  - [x] Extract iteration number from `[LOOP] iteration N` messages\n    88→  - [x] Handle in run.ts directly via `currentIterationCount` variable\n    89→\n    90→- [x] Task 4: Accumulate cost from result events (AC: #7)\n    91→  - [x] In `ink-renderer.tsx`, update `result` event handler to accumulate cost\n    92→  - [x] Extract `cost` from `result` event payload (already parsed by stream-parser as `cost_usd`)\n    93→  - [x] Update `SprintInfo.totalCost` directly in the result event handler\n    94→\n    95→- [x] Task 5: Update all existing tests (AC: #9)\n    96→  - [x] Update Header test — assert no Box border in output, assert plain text header format\n    97→  - [x] Update StoryBreakdown test — assert labeled sections (`Done:`, `This:`, `Next:`, `Blocked:`)\n    98→  - [x] Update App integration tests for new layout\n    99→  - [x] Ensure all 2889 tests pass with new component structure (0 regressions)\n   100→\n   101→- [x] Task 6: Add visual snapshot test (AC: #10)\n   102→  - [x] Create known RendererState with populated sprint info, stories, messages\n   103→  - [x] Render App with ink-testing-library\n   104→  - [x] Assert output contains exact header format line\n   105→  - [x] Assert output contains `━━━` separators\n   106→  - [x] Assert output contains labeled story sections (`Done:`, `This:`, `Next:`)\n   107→  - [x] Assert output matches spec format structure\n   108→\n   109→## Dev Notes\n   110→\n   111→### What Exists (Rewrite, Not Enhance)\n   112→\n   113→Unlike story 0-5-3 which enhanced existing components, this story REWRITES the visual layout. The underlying state management (`RendererState`, `update()`, `updateSprintState()`, etc.) is correct and should be preserved. The components that render the state need restructuring.\n   114→\n   115→### Key Divergences from Current Implementation\n   116→\n   117→| Current | Spec | Fix |\n   118→|---------|------|-----|\n   119→| `<Box borderStyle=\"round\">` header | Plain text `codeharness run \\| iteration N \\| ...` | Remove Box, use Text |\n   120→| `◆ {storyKey} — {phase} \\| {elapsed} \\| Sprint: {done}/{total}` | `codeharness run \\| iteration N \\| Xm elapsed \\| $Y.ZZ spent` | Different header content entirely |\n   121→| No `Story:` / `Phase:` lines | Separate lines below separator | Add new lines |\n   122→| Horizontal compact `N ✓ done \\| ◆ key \\| next: key` | Vertical `Done:` / `This:` / `Next:` / `Blocked:` | Rewrite StoryBreakdown |\n   123→| No iteration count | `iteration N` in header | Parse from `[LOOP]` stderr |\n   124→| No cost tracking | `$Y.ZZ spent` in header | Accumulate from `result` events |\n   125→| No `━━━` separators | Full-width `━━━` lines | Add separator component |\n   126→\n   127→### Key Files to Modify\n   128→\n   129→- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — Rewrite Header, StoryBreakdown, add Separator; expand SprintInfo type\n   130→- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — Accumulate cost from result events; update SprintInfo with new fields\n   131→- `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` — Parse `[LOOP]` iteration messages from ralph stderr\n   132→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Wire iteration count and cost into SprintInfo updates\n   133→- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` — Update all component tests\n   134→\n   135→### Key Files to Read (Do NOT Modify)\n   136→\n   137→- `src/lib/stream-parser.ts` — StreamEvent types (check `result` event shape for cost field)\n   138→- `_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-specification.md` lines 197-253 — The spec to match\n   139→\n   140→### Architecture Constraints\n   141→\n   142→- **NFR9: No file > 300 lines.** ink-components.tsx is currently 252 lines. The rewrite should stay under 300. If it exceeds, split into `ink-layout-components.tsx` (Header, Separator, StoryBreakdown) and `ink-activity-components.tsx` (tools, thoughts, retry).\n   143→- **Vitest** for unit tests, **100% coverage target**\n   144→- **ink-testing-library** for component rendering tests\n   145→- **TSX** with `\"jsx\": \"react-jsx\"` in tsconfig\n   146→\n   147→### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n   148→\n   149→- Do NOT use `console.log` — Ink manages the terminal\n   150→- Do NOT use raw ANSI escape codes for colors — use Ink's `<Text>` color props\n   151→- Do NOT break the RendererHandle API — consumers (run.ts) depend on the existing interface\n   152→- Do NOT change the event handling logic in ink-renderer.tsx — only add cost accumulation to `result` handler\n   153→- Do NOT hardcode terminal width — use `process.stdout.columns` with a fallback\n   154→\n   155→### References\n   156→\n   157→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-specification.md#Lines 197-253] — live mode display format (THE spec to match)\n   158→- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx] — current components to rewrite\n   159→- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx] — controller (preserve API, update result handler)\n   160→- [Source: src/lib/run-helpers.ts] — add [LOOP] parsing\n   161→- [Source: src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx] — tests to update\n   162→\n   163→## Dev Agent Record\n   164→\n   165→### Implementation Plan\n   166→\n   167→1. Rewrote Header component: removed Box border, plain text `codeharness run | ...` format, added Separator, Story/Phase lines\n   168→2. Rewrote StoryBreakdown: vertical labeled sections (Done/This/Next/Blocked) with retry counts\n   169→3. Added `parseIterationMessage()` to run-helpers.ts for `[LOOP]` stderr parsing\n   170→4. Added cost accumulation in ink-renderer.tsx result event handler\n   171→5. Wired iteration count tracking in run.ts via `currentIterationCount` variable\n   172→6. Split ink-components.tsx into 3 files to comply with NFR9