{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XQyRi8Dn7P7ciZXCw86xcd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VicuWqmZYh7CGobM6rV9dA","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /tmp/codeharness-verify-6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec && claude --print --max-budget-usd 5 --allowedTools Bash Read Write Glob Grep Edit -p \"You are a black-box verifier. Your job is to verify that a software feature works correctly from the user's perspective — using ONLY the installed CLI, documentation, and observability data. You have NO access to source code.\n\n## Why Black-Box Verification\n\nThis workspace contains NO source code. The src/ directory does not exist. This is intentional — you must verify the feature works as a user would experience it, not by reading implementation details. If you cannot verify a feature from docs + CLI alone, that is a REAL failure in the product's documentation or packaging.\n\n## Step 1: Read README.md\n\nStart by reading README.md in this workspace. It contains install and usage instructions for the project. Use it to understand how to exercise the CLI.\n\n## Step 2: Review Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe story file story.md contains the acceptance criteria you must verify. Read it now.\n\n## Step 3: Verify Each AC\n\nFor EACH acceptance criterion, you must:\n\n1. Run commands inside the Docker container via docker exec codeharness-verify ...\n2. Capture the command output as evidence\n3. Query observability endpoints if runtime evidence is needed\n\n### Docker Container\n\n- Container name: codeharness-verify\n- ALL CLI commands MUST run via: docker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n- Example: docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness --version\n\nThe container has the following tools installed:\n- codeharness — the project CLI\n- claude — Claude Code CLI (authenticated via ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env var)\n- curl, jq — for querying observability endpoints\n- node, npm — Node.js runtime\n\n**IMPORTANT:** This story is about Ink terminal UI components. To verify the rendering output without running a full sprint, use node inside the container to import and render the components. The dist/ bundle is installed globally. You can:\n\n1. Use docker exec codeharness-verify node -e '...' to run JS that exercises the rendering\n2. Use docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness --help to check CLI availability\n3. Check that the npm package exports the needed types and functions\n\nFor Ink component verification, the key approach is:\n- Import the dist bundle and check exported types/functions\n- If possible, exercise the renderer with mock data to see actual output\n- Check that the CLI integrates the new components correctly\n\n### Project Type: Node.js CLI\n\nExecute commands inside the container and capture stdout/stderr as evidence:\n- docker exec codeharness-verify <cli-command> [args]\n- Capture exit codes: docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c '<command>; echo EXIT:\\$?'\n- For Node.js projects, the built artifact is installed globally in the container.\n\n### Observability Endpoints\n\nQuery these from the HOST (not inside the container) for runtime evidence:\n\n- **VictoriaLogs** (logs): http://localhost:9428\n  - Example: curl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&limit=10'\n- **VictoriaMetrics** (metrics): http://localhost:8428\n  - Example: curl 'http://localhost:8428/api/v1/query?query=up'\n\n## Step 3.5: Observability Check\n\nAfter key docker exec commands, query VictoriaLogs for recent log events.\n\n## Step 4: Write Proof Document\n\nWrite your verification proof to: verification/6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec-proof.md\n\nUse this format for each AC:\n\n\\`\\`\\`markdown\n## AC N: <description>\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n\\`\\`\\`output\n<actual output>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**IMPORTANT: Only use bash and output as code fence languages.** Never use bare \\`\\`\\` fences without a language tag.\n\n## Critical Rules\n\n1. **ALL commands MUST use docker exec codeharness-verify ...** — do NOT run commands directly on the host filesystem.\n2. **Do NOT attempt to access source code** — there is no src/ directory in this workspace.\n3. **Report REAL failures** — if a feature does not work, report that as a verification failure. Do NOT fabricate passing evidence.\n4. **Every AC needs functional evidence** — reading docs alone is not evidence. You must execute commands and capture output.\n5. **[ESCALATE] is ONLY for things that are genuinely impossible to automate** — NOT for infrastructure problems.\n6. **Never switch to unit-testable verification.** If Docker verification doesnt work, report WHY as a [FAIL].\" 2>&1","description":"Run black-box verifier for story 6-1","timeout":600000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":291,"cache_read_input_tokens":55724,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":291},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"81bb0af8-322d-4529-9f90-f01a7df366b2","uuid":"96c8b72d-92a9-4d19-adf0-33654269a91c"}
